summary:
The Security Council,
Reaffirming previous resolutions 242, 338, 1397, and the Madrid principles,
Expressing grave concern at the situation's deterioration, including recent suicide bombings and a military attack on the Palestinian Authority's headquarters,
1. Calls for an immediate ceasefire, Israeli troop withdrawal from Palestinian cities, and cooperation with Special Envoy Zinni to implement the Tenet security work plan towards resuming negotiations;
2. Demands an immediate cessation of all acts of violence, terror, provocation, incitement, and destruction;
3. Supports the Secretary-General and special envoys' efforts to halt violence and resume the peace process;
4. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
